definitions.definition: A burning serpent , often winged, with human hands and sometimes feet; one of God 's entourage. On Earth, they strike with burning poison; in Heaven, with burning coal. A description can be found at the beginning of Isaiah chapter 6 .
A six-winged angel ; one of the highest choir or order of angels in Christian angelology , ranked above cherubim , and below God.
